rag_answer:
The correct JSON structure for sending a function result back to the Mistral API in a conversation handoff is as follows:

```json
{
    "inputs": [
        {
            "type": "function.result",
            "tool_call_id": "<tool_call_id>",
            "result": "<result_data>"
        }
    ],
    "stream": false,
    "agent_id": "<agent_id>"
}
```

This structure is shown in **[1]** and **[5]** (curl examples). Key fields:
- `type`: Must be `"function.result"`
- `tool_call_id`: The ID of the tool call being responded to
- `result`: The output of the function (can be a string or JSON string)

Example from **[5]** (curl tab):
```json
{
    "inputs": [
        {
            "tool_call_id": "6TI17yZkV",
            "result": "{\"date\": \"2024-06-06\", \"interest_rate\": \"2.5%\"}",
            "object": "entry",
            "type": "function.result"
        }
    ],
    ...
}
```

